The genesis of this project, this resurrected icon, began in June 2022. It was an initiative born from the mind of Jean-Philippe Imparato, the man at the helm of [Alfa Romeo](/Alfa_Romeo). He managed to salvage and repurpose development work from a project that, for reasons lost to the annals of corporate history, had been abandoned. This discarded work, ironically, had been intended for the [Maserati MC20](/Maserati_MC20), a supercar in its own right. It’s a curious twist of fate, isn't it? A forgotten seed, blossoming into something entirely new, yet deeply familiar. &#91;6&#93; &#91;7&#93;

The entire endeavor is a deliberate homage, a reverent nod to the original 1967 [Alfa Romeo 33 Stradale](/Alfa_Romeo_33_Stradale). That car was a legend, a whisper of pure performance and breathtaking design. This new iteration is no different, except in its exclusivity. Production is strictly limited, a mere 33 units. Thirty-three chances to own a piece of automotive art. Production is slated to commence in June 2024, a date circled in red on the calendars of collectors and enthusiasts alike. The actual construction, the meticulous assembly of these masterpieces, is entrusted to the esteemed Italian coach-building firm, [Touring Superleggera](/Carrozzeria_Touring_Superleggera). They are the artisans who will breathe life into these limited-edition dreams. &#91;8&#93; &#91;9&#93;

